  {
    "type": "text",
    "tag": "start-intro",
    "text": "We have divided ideologies in two of the main axes for Catalan politics: the desired relationship with Spain, and the traditional left-right spectrum from social and economic point of views. With this app, we pinpoint where you are compared with the rest of the Catalan population. Click on the colored squares to find out how the 25 clusters are different. What do you think, where do most people stand? And where would you be positioned in this raster?"
  },
  {
    "type": "text",
    "tag": "explanation",
    "text": "We have used all the political barometer surveys the Catalan Opinion Studies Center (CEO) has conducted in the past decade and taken into account the 41,838 polls they have made since 2014. We have grouped the individuals in clusters of political affinity guessing their ideology in both axes by analysing their answers to key questions about social and economic affairs."
  },
  {
    "type": "text",
    "tag": "top-left",
    "text": "This is the most typical political group. They are the individuals within the top 20% most pro-independence feeling among all residents and the top 20% more left-leaning. What do we know about them? All of them have Catalan as their usual language, most of them have superior studies (59%) and over a third are aged 35 to 49 (35%)."
  },
